.TH SET_MAKEFILE_PACKAGE 1 "$Date: 2000-05-23 23:27:06 $"
.SH NAME
set_makefile_package\- reset the PACKAGE macro in a makefile
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
set_makefile_package new_package_value
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
This command resets the assignment of the PACKAGE= macro in all 
makefiles named Makefile that are in the current directory or 
subdirectories of the current directory. If no assignment exists, 
a new macro assignment value is entered right before the
include $(ANTELOPEMAKE) line. 
.SH OPTIONS
.SH FILES
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.SH PARAMETER FILE
.SH EXAMPLE
.ft CW
.RS .2i
.RE
.ft R
.nf
array% set_makefile_package '$(ANTELOPE)/contrib'
array%
.fi
.SH RETURN VALUES
.SH LIBRARY
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.nf
antelopemake(5)
.fi
.SH "BUGS AND CAVEATS"
If the macro refers to other environment variables or macros, the specification
must be enclosed in single quotes to protect it from shell expansion
.SH AUTHOR
.nf
Kent Lindquist
Geophysical Institute
.fi
